<emphasis box="[1130,1278,1609,1634]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Quercus ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1335,1436,1609,1635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suber">
<emphasis box="[1335,1356,1609,1634]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Q</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1371,1436,1609,1634]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">suber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees along a stream, and this is the first record for the island. A single specimen was hand-collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[1367,1435,1648,1674]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Sicily</collectingRegion>
in a clearing of a 
<taxonomicName box="[370,475,1687,1713]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suber">
<emphasis box="[370,391,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Q</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[408,475,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">suber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest, being a new record for this region, whereas the Tuscan record may be occasional, the single specimen having been collected on a car.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1029,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Other localities are in 
<collectingRegion box="[463,551,1764,1790]" country="Italy" name="Lazio" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Latium</collectingRegion>
, where 
<specimenCount box="[643,805,1764,1790]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
from the Latina province was collected by a Malaise trap placed in a 
<taxonomicName box="[335,412,1802,1828]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ilex">
<emphasis box="[335,356,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Q</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[370,412,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest with isolated 
<taxonomicName box="[649,749,1802,1828]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suber">
<emphasis box="[649,670,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Q</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[684,749,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">suber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees (San Felice Circeo, Circeo National Park) (
<emphasis box="[1321,1342,1803,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">cf</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mason, F. &amp; Cerretti, P. &amp; Nardi, G. &amp; Whitmore, D. &amp; Birtele, D. &amp; Hardersen, S. &amp; Gatti, E." pageId="1" pageNumber="422" pagination="51 - 70" refId="ref3821" refString="Mason, F., Cerretti, P., Nardi, G., Whitmore, D., Birtele, D., Hardersen, S. &amp; Gatti, E. (2006) Aspects of biological diversity in the CONECOFOR plots. IV. The Invertebrate Biodiv pilot project. In: Ferretti, M., Petriccione, B., Bussotti, F. &amp; Fabbio, G. (Eds), Aspects of biodiversity in selected forest ecosystems in Italy: status and changes over the period 1996 - 2003. Third report of the Task Force on Integrated and Combined (I &amp; C) evaluation of the CONECOFOR programme. Annali dell'Istituto Sperimentale per la Selvicoltura, 30 (Suppl. 2), 51 - 70." type="journal article" year="2006">
Mason 
<emphasis box="[151,203,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
), whereas those from the Viterbo province were already recorded as 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1269,1841,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Tropideres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1101,1227,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Tropideres</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vannini, A. &amp; Biocca, M. &amp; Paparatti, B." pageId="1" pageNumber="422" pagination="53 - 55" refId="ref4322" refString="Vannini, A., Biocca, M. &amp; Paparatti, B. (1996) Contributo alla conoscenza del ciclo biologico di Hypoxylon mediterraneum su Quercus cerris. L'Informatore fitopatologico, 66 (9), 53 - 55." type="journal article" year="1996">
Vannini 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">et al</emphasis>
. (1996)
</bibRefCitation>
. As stated by these authors, these specimens were reared from dead wood of 
<taxonomicName box="[1182,1286,1880,1906]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerris">
<emphasis box="[1182,1203,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Q</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1218,1286,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with mature stroma of 
<taxonomicName box="[272,589,1919,1944]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mediterraneum">
<emphasis box="[272,589,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Hypoxylon mediterraneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pyrenomycetes, Sphaeriales, 
<taxonomicName box="[955,1101,1919,1945]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Xylariaceae</taxonomicName>
), the beetles probably being vectors of the fungus. Also other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[725,877,1957,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anthribidae</taxonomicName>
are known to feed on 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1305,1957,1982]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1305,1957,1982]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Hypoxylon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other pyrenomycete fungi (
<bibRefCitation author="Valentine, B. D." box="[401,584,1996,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" pagination="251 - 296" refId="ref4284" refString="Valentine, B. D. (1999) A review of Nearctic and some related Anthribidae (Coleoptera). Insecta Mundi, 12 (3 - 4) [1998], 251 - 296." type="journal article" year="1999">Valentine 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
These new records indicate that 
<taxonomicName box="[596,732,152,178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Araecerodes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grenieri">
<emphasis box="[596,620,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[639,732,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">grenieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably more widespread in 
<collectingCountry box="[1140,1195,152,178]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Italy</collectingCountry>
. It is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,221,190,216]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Spain</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[342,425,190,216]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[437,529,190,216]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Corsica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[542,648,190,216]" name="Slovakia" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[660,748,190,216]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffmann, A." box="[764,955,190,216]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" refId="ref3548" refString="Hoffmann, A. (1945) Coleopteres Bruchides et Anthribides (avec 434 figures). Faune de France, 44. Lechevalier, Paris, 184 pp." type="book" year="1945">Hoffmann 1945</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[1000,1217,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Choragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grenieri">
<emphasis box="[1000,1217,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Choragus grenieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Strejcek, J." box="[1234,1398,190,216]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" pagination="134" refId="ref4176" refString="Strejcek, J. (1993) Anthribidae. In: Jelinek, J. (Ed.), Checklist of Czechoslovak Insect IV (Coleoptera) Seznam c eskolovenskych brouk u. Folia Heyrovskyana, Suppl. 1, p. 134." type="journal article" year="1993">Strejček 1993</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="C. Brisout" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[151,423,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Melanopsacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grenieri">
<emphasis box="[151,423,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Melanopsacus grenieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rheinheimer, J." box="[440,664,229,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" pagination="1 - 243" refId="ref4106" refString="Rheinheimer, J. (2004) Illustrierter Katalog und Bibliographie der Anthribidae der Welt (Insecta: Coleoptera). Mitteilungen des Entomologischen Vereins Stuttgart, 39 (1 - 2), 1 - 243." type="journal article" year="2004">Rheinheimer 2004</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[685,786,229,255]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[846,936,229,255]" name="Finland" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Finland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A." box="[952,1228,229,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" refId="ref3072" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. (2004) Fauna Europaea: Anthribidae, Apionidae, Curculionidae. In: Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Europaea: Coleoptera 1. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, available at http: // www. faunaeur. org [accessed September 2009 as version 1.3 of April 19 th 2007.]" type="url" year="2004">Alonso-Zarazaga 2004</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brisout" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Araeocerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grenieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Araeocerodes grenieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
As for its biology, the few data given by the above authors and the new records indicate that the species lives on 
<taxonomicName box="[253,410,345,371]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[253,352,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Quercus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
Most probably adults are night flyers and their association with pyrenomycete fungi, often ignored by most entomologists, can explain why 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="C. Brisout" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[795,1064,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Melanopsacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grenieri">
<emphasis box="[795,1064,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Melanopsacus grenieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so infrequently collected.
</paragraph>
